<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by Alan Jordan, owner of Jordan Products Ltd</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:center"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Alan Jordan, owner of Jordan Products Ltd (SRN 051)</span></p><p style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Having established my own design and manufacturing business in Ballyclare, Northern Ireland, I have worked with the Highways Agency (HA) since 2002 to develop a fully HA-approved </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">mechanised system (Conemaster) to lift and lay traffic cones on the Strategic Road Network with new levels of speed, efficiency and safety. My reason for this submission is to set out how Conemaster can improve the network for all users and to draw on my o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">wn experience with HA to illustrate the need for its reform. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Conemaster is a British product which has been independently assessed by the International company Jacobs. It</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s report in February 2012 accepted that Conemaster had the potential to save lives, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to provide high value for money and to reduce congestion across the HA strategic road network. Despite being market ready and available since 2006, powerful vested interests working, in my view, with HA have ensured that Conemaster remains excluded from en</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tering the home market. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:13pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Cambria; font-size:13pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The approach to Road Worker Safety within the HA is in need of urgent and sweeping reform. The real picture regarding road worker incidents has been hidden for many years by systematic under-reporting. Recent fi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">gures provide an alarming picture</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">*</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">(See section 3.6 below)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> *</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">compared with 2011, the total number of s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tatutory</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> reportable incidents involving road worker</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> has risen from 47 to a staggering 1747 incidents for the last 12 month period.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">**</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">(See section </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">1.1 below)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> **</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The “Actions for Roads” paper says little about safety. It suggests, however, that continuous improvement seeks to develop, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“technical innovations and behavioural measures to ensure road works are delivered safely”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> :</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the HA’s handling of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Conemaster starkly illustrates that this is not part of the culture that exists in the HA or the industry today. There is unlikely to be a change in this direction without the Government (or the Committee) holding the HA (and its major contractors) more ro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">bustly to account.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">(See section 3. below)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">iii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Action for roads states that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“A single incident that closes a three-lane motorway for four hours can cost several million pounds in lost time, and there </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">are some 80,000 incidents that impact at least one motorway </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">lane each year.”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">(Source: Action for Roads - page47 sect3.44)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">very significantly, the Jacobs report accepted that Conemaster would save at least 30 minutes per road closure for the installation and removal of traffic cones and lamps with the resulting fin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ancial efficiencies – despite this the industry (and HA) have been unwilling to invest in the new technology. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">iv)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Jacobs report accepted that Conemaster would significantly improve road worker safety, reduce congestion, and offer savings of around £5.5m </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">per year. It assessed Conemaster as a “high value for money” product with a benefit to cost ratio of 2.06</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">*</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">From the results it can be seen 13,000 hours per year of extra lane availability is achievable across the Strategic Road Network.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">**   </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">*</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> Jacobs Feb 2012 report p7 sect 3.1 and p18-19 sect14 b.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">** </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">extrapolated from 26,000 closures per year X 30 minute saving per closure = 13,000 hours extra lane availability.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">furthermore, endorsements have been received from 2 Transport Ministers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">(10th Aug</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> 2006 and 9th July 2012.)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">; and</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">despite the independent report and the Ministers’ views, the five major companies to whom we wrote and e-mailed, on the advice of the Minister at the time, did not acknowledge or reply – this illustrates, further, the lack </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of interest in addressing seriously issues of safety, efficiency and congestion.. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">v)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The HA has clearly either lacked the appropriate data or mis-used data. This was particularly evident during the Jacobs review process:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Dr McCrea M.P. found it necessary t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o ask PQs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">[92139 &amp; 92140] </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to reveal simple facts about the total number of road closures in the course of a year. The HA’s initial figures, typically 120,000</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">*</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> road closures per year became 25,713 road closures for 2011</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">*HA Conemaster Cost Study for the M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">inister  29</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:5.33pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold"> June 2011 - Annex 1: Detailed calculations relating to Automated Cone Laying Machines.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Typically costing £1000 per closure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">*</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, this represented a difference in costs of around £90m per year potentially.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">*</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">HA Conemaster Cost Study for the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">Minister  29</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:5.33pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold"> June 2011 - Annex 1: Detailed calculations relating to Automated Cone Laying Machines.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="